sks, avg 54.5 steps, successRate=1 but 2 errors. Steps are over the 40-step rewo
rk budget.\n\nLet me think about the most impactful improvements:\n\n### dev (Cr
itical issues):\n- 108 steps average (over 60-step hard limit!) - This suggests 
the "硬上限" at line 135 is text-only and the agent is ignoring it, OR the agent
doesn\'t reliably self-monitor.\n- 2 errors from 1 task\n- 76 Shell calls and 36
ReadFile calls - massive tool usage\n- **Root cause**: The prompt has an interna
l self-policing mechanism (step counting in head + self-report every 10 steps + 
hard stop at 60), but the agent isn\'t obeying it. We need to make the enforceme
nt more concrete - perhaps adding a stronger step-counting mechanism at the begi
nning.\n\n### review (Critical issues):\n- 100% error rate (both tasks had error
s)\n- 24 avg steps is reasonable\n- **Root cause**: The prompt\'s "遇到错误时快
速跳过" (line 225) and "错误熔断" (line 226) say to stop after 2 consecutive err
ors, but maybe the errors are coming from gh commands or ReadFile failures that 
are being triggered and counted as errors but not stopping the agent. Looking at
the report: 3 total errors from 2 tasks. The agent is probably trying `gh pr dif
f` or similar commands that fail, then continuing.\n\n### e2e (Critical issues):
